techmeme.title: Estonian ride-hailing and food delivery startup Bolt says it hit €2B in annual revenue and plans a 2025 IPO; Bolt had an $8B+ valuation in January 2022 (Alessandro Parodi/Reuters)
JD.com reports Q3 revenue up 5.1% YoY to ~$36B, above $35.9B est., and net income up 48% YoY to ~$1.6B, suggesting a recovery in segments of China's economy (Bloomberg)
Sonos reports Q4 revenue down 8% YoY to $1.5B, spent $4M on "app recovery investments", and has released 16 app updates and "restored 90% of missing features" (Chris Welch/The Verge)
Apple releases updates to Final Cut Pro, adding AI-generated closed captions and Vision Pro spatial video editing, and Logic Pro for macOS and iPadOS (John Voorhees/MacStories)
A look at "blind box livestreaming", an e-commerce trend in China that has become an entertaining and, some users and experts said, addictive pastime (New York Times)
